id.description: The ID used to identify this component in Dash callbacks

setProps.description:
Dash-assigned callback that should be called whenever any of the
properties change

hiddenAttributes.description: contains attribute names to omit from the UI

hiddenFromAggregators.description: contains attribute names to omit from the aggregator arguments dropdowns

hiddenFromDragDrop.description: contains attribute names to omit from the drag'n'drop portion of the UI

menuLimit.description: maximum number of values to list in the double-click menu

unusedOrientationCutoff.description:
If the attributes' names' combined length in characters exceeds this
value then the unused attributes area will be shown vertically to the
left of the UI instead of horizontally above it. 0 therefore means
'always vertical', and Infinity means 'always horizontal'.

cols.description: Which columns are currently in the column area

colOrder.description:
the order in which column data is provided to the renderer, must be one
of "key_a_to_z", "value_a_to_z", "value_z_to_a", ordering by value
orders by column total

rows.description: Which rows is currently inside the row area.

rowOrder.description:
the order in which row data is provided to the renderer, must be one
of "key_a_to_z", "value_a_to_z", "value_z_to_a", ordering by value
orders by row total

aggregatorName.description: Which aggregator is currently selected. E.g. Count, Sum, Average, etc.

rendererName.description:
Which renderer is currently selected. E.g. Table, Line Chart, Scatter
Chart, etc.
